@HeyaHoyah Er... are you really trying to make _logic rules_ about _dreams?_ It looks like those dream interpretation dictionaries, mate ^^'.
For the record, I've had countless dreams where I know _exactly_ how I got where. Sometimes I go from my home to a mall. Sometimes I drive from a city to a certain place in the country. I don't just pop somewhere in those dreams, I see the whole travel.


My point is, there are no such rules as "you don't know how you got to a place." In fact, *there are no rules **_at all_** when we're talking about dreams.* Dreams are imaginary by their very nature. You can imagine you pop up to a place, or you can imagine the whole way...

@sir-dolphino Yes, Nolan told him "all of your scenes are YOUR reality". Not "objective" reality.
Because the whole POINT of Inception is to convey the message that reality is subjective. Pretending that the end has an answer, is failing to understand the whole point of the movie.
Again: sheer misinterpretation of the facts.

