It's comments like this which prove how awesome Inception is.  It gets people thinking and they start unraveling their imaginations.  The ending isn't supposed to give us an answer, but it tells us to make up our own minds what we think it means.

It's a real damn shame there aren't enough movies that do this.  Any movie that drives its viewers to talk about its mysteries for months and months after its release deserves a high place on the "best films ever made" list.

